to deal with.

00:14:30.700 --> 00:14:34.090 align:middle line:90%


00:14:34.090 --> 00:14:37.420 align:middle line:84%
We know that anxiety
is healthy and normal,

00:14:37.420 --> 00:14:40.570 align:middle line:84%
and it happens to all
of us some of the time.

00:14:40.570 --> 00:14:43.230 align:middle line:90%


00:14:43.230 --> 00:14:45.480 align:middle line:84%
Anxiety is a
response in your body

00:14:45.480 --> 00:14:50.770 align:middle line:84%
to make you alert, prepared,
and ready to act when it's

00:14:50.770 --> 00:14:52.360 align:middle line:90%
necessary for your benefit.

00:14:52.360 --> 00:14:55.180 align:middle line:90%


00:14:55.180 --> 00:14:57.300 align:middle line:84%
But for now, you've
allowed your anxiety

00:14:57.300 --> 00:15:02.270 align:middle line:84%
to become too
alert, too fearful,

00:15:02.270 --> 00:15:05.330 align:middle line:84%
and it's now time to allow
your anxiety some time

00:15:05.330 --> 00:15:12.280 align:middle line:84%
to refocus, review,
to do its job better,

00:15:12.280 --> 00:15:14.760 align:middle line:90%
return to helping you.

00:15:14.760 --> 00:15:16.820 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
do that right now.

00:15:16.820 --> 00:15:23.550 align:middle line:90%


00:15:23.550 --> 00:15:26.580 align:middle line:84%
And you're conscious of the
gentle beating of your heart

00:15:26.580 --> 00:15:29.880 align:middle line:84%
and the steady rhythm
of each breath,

00:15:29.880 --> 00:15:38.485 align:middle line:84%
breathing gently and
slowly, slowly and evenly.

00:15:38.485 --> 00:15:43.230 align:middle line:90%


00:15:43.230 --> 00:15:45.270 align:middle line:84%
And it's time to
realize that you

00:15:45.270 --> 00:15:50.580 align:middle line:84%
are in control of your
thoughts as your beliefs

00:15:50.580 --> 00:15:53.740 align:middle line:84%
are just thoughts that have
been thought over time and time

00:15:53.740 --> 00:15:54.540 align:middle line:90%
again.

00:15:54.540 --> 00:15:58.400 align:middle line:90%


00:15:58.400 --> 00:16:00.860 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps you've been thinking
too much that you're not

00:16:00.860 --> 00:16:02.960 align:middle line:84%
good enough or
you've been worrying

00:16:02.960 --> 00:16:05.630 align:middle line:84%
about something
out of your control

00:16:05.630 --> 00:16:10.095 align:middle line:84%
or a situation, fear, or phobia
has been holding you back.

00:16:10.095 --> 00:16:13.530 align:middle line:90%


00:16:13.530 --> 00:16:18.000 align:middle line:84%
We can simply replace those
old, unwanted thoughts, now,

00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:20.350 align:middle line:84%
with new, empowering,
positive ones.

00:16:20.350 --> 00:16:24.180 align:middle line:90%


00:16:24.180 --> 00:16:26.940 align:middle line:84%
It's time, now, to stop
imagining the worst

00:16:26.940 --> 00:16:30.350 align:middle line:84%
is about to happen when
good things await you.

00:16:30.350 --> 00:16:35.990 align:middle line:90%


00:16:35.990 --> 00:16:39.970 align:middle line:84%
As we free ourselves
now of panic or anxiety

00:16:39.970 --> 00:16:44.330 align:middle line:84%
or whichever symptoms have
been generated in the past,

00:16:44.330 --> 00:16:48.580 align:middle line:84%
we replace them with
feelings of calmness,

00:16:48.580 --> 00:16:52.850 align:middle line:84%
feelings of confidence, control,
and optimism for the future.

00:16:52.850 --> 00:16:58.240 align:middle line:90%


00:16:58.240 --> 00:17:03.900 align:middle line:84%
And every time you discharge one
of those symptoms of anxiety,

00:17:03.900 --> 00:17:05.730 align:middle line:84%
you will replace
them with a feeling

00:17:05.730 --> 00:17:10.410 align:middle line:84%
of being calm,
relaxed, optimistic,

00:17:10.410 --> 00:17:12.630 align:middle line:90%
and confident for things ahead.

00:17:12.630 --> 00:17:18.940 align:middle line:90%


00:17:18.940 --> 00:17:23.050 align:middle line:84%
You know that anxiety and
fear are very different.

00:17:23.050 --> 00:17:25.210 align:middle line:84%
Fear is what you
feel in the moment--

00:17:25.210 --> 00:17:28.060 align:middle line:84%
when you're watching a
scary film, for example.

00:17:28.060 --> 00:17:31.800 align:middle line:90%
And fear makes a lot of sense.

00:17:31.800 --> 00:17:36.200 align:middle line:84%
But anxiety's about the
anticipation of an event.

00:17:36.200 --> 00:17:40.280 align:middle line:84%
Anxiety is your brain asking
what if too many times

00:17:40.280 --> 00:17:42.770 align:middle line:84%
and coming up with a lot
of answers it doesn't like.

00:17:42.770 --> 00:17:46.120 align:middle line:90%


00:17:46.120 --> 00:17:50.000 align:middle line:90%
But you don't know the future.

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:54.330 align:middle line:84%
That what-if may
not even happen.

00:17:54.330 --> 00:17:57.290 align:middle line:84%
So anxiety is often
problem solving,

00:17:57.290 --> 00:17:58.970 align:middle line:90%
but without the solving part.

00:17:58.970 --> 00:18:01.780 align:middle line:90%


00:18:01.780 --> 00:18:04.420 align:middle line:84%
From now on, you no
longer worry about things

00:18:04.420 --> 00:18:08.540 align:middle line:84%
that may happen in the
future, things that might

00:18:08.540 --> 00:18:11.420 align:middle line:90%
make you feel out of control.

00:18:11.420 --> 00:18:14.180 align:middle line:84%
And you learn to live much
more in the moment, day

00:18:14.180 --> 00:18:19.350 align:middle line:84%
by day, as you take
each day at a time,

00:18:19.350 --> 00:18:20.835 align:middle line:90%
being present and mindful.

00:18:20.835 --> 00:18:25.890 align:middle line:90%


00:18:25.890 --> 00:18:28.050 align:middle line:84%
And you release the
tension of worrying

00:18:28.050 --> 00:18:30.720 align:middle line:84%
about things in the future
that you can't control.

00:18:30.720 --> 00:18:32.520 align:middle line:90%
You take each day at a time.

00:18:32.520 --> 00:18:39.270 align:middle line:90%


00:18:39.270 --> 00:18:43.020 align:middle line:84%
You remember that the body can't
fail two conflicting emotions

00:18:43.020 --> 00:18:44.490 align:middle line:90%
at once.

00:18:44.490 --> 00:18:49.600 align:middle line:84%
So whenever you feel yourself
tensing or anxiety rising,

00:18:49.600 --> 00:18:53.030 align:middle line:90%
all you need to do is slow down.

00:18:53.030 --> 00:18:55.300 align:middle line:90%
Breathe in.

00:18:55.300 --> 00:18:56.360 align:middle line:90%
And breathe out.

00:18:56.360 --> 00:19:00.190 align:middle line:90%
And allow your body to relax.

00:19:00.190 --> 00:19:02.230 align:middle line:84%
If you have your
breathing under control,

00:19:02.230 --> 00:19:06.520 align:middle line:84%
gentle breaths in and
out, your body and mind

00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:10.090 align:middle line:84%
will have no choice but to
slow down, to ground yourself.

00:19:10.090 --> 00:19:12.580 align:middle line:90%
Your thinking will slow.

00:19:12.580 --> 00:19:15.280 align:middle line:84%
Your heartbeat returns
to its normal pace.

00:19:15.280 --> 00:19:18.220 align:middle line:90%


00:19:18.220 --> 00:19:20.380 align:middle line:84%
Those feelings of
anxiety will be

00:19:20.380 --> 00:19:24.130 align:middle line:84%
replaced with calm and
stillness, gentle breaths

00:19:24.130 --> 00:19:27.270 align:middle line:90%
in and out again.

00:19:27.270 --> 00:19:32.330 align:middle line:90%


00:19:32.330 --> 00:19:36.050 align:middle line:84%
So let's do a breathing
technique now.

00:19:36.050 --> 00:19:39.650 align:middle line:84%
I'd like you to breathe
in for four seconds,

00:19:39.650 --> 00:19:43.890 align:middle line:84%
hold for four seconds,
and breathe out for six,

00:19:43.890 --> 00:19:45.260 align:middle line:90%
starting now.

00:19:45.260 --> 00:19:50.700 align:middle line:90%
Breathe in for 1, 2, 3, 4.

00:19:50.700 --> 00:19:55.050 align:middle line:90%
Hold for 1, 2, 3, 4.

00:19:55.050 --> 00:20:03.340 align:middle line:84%
And release for 1,
2, 3, 4, 5, and 6.

00:20:03.340 --> 00:20:08.450 align:middle line:84%
And you find a pace
that's right for you,

00:20:08.450 --> 00:20:10.850 align:middle line:84%
but using that
technique to calm you,

00:20:10.850 --> 00:20:13.280 align:middle line:84%
to ground you when your
thoughts and your mind

00:20:13.280 --> 00:20:14.480 align:middle line:90%
seem out of control--

00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:18.695 align:middle line:84%
in for four, hold for
four, and out for six.

00:20:18.695 --> 00:20:23.210 align:middle line:90%


00:20:23.210 --> 00:20:25.490 align:middle line:84%
Whenever you feel
anxious now, you simply

00:20:25.490 --> 00:20:28.610 align:middle line:84%
use that breathing
technique to flip the body

00:20:28.610 --> 00:20:34.060 align:middle line:84%
from feeling anxious into a
state of calm and relaxation.

00:20:34.060 --> 00:20:38.000 align:middle line:90%


00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:44.140 align:middle line:84%
You feel yourself free, such
a relief, such a release.

00:20:44.140 --> 00:20:48.590 align:middle line:84%
Taking every day as it
comes, taking back control,

00:20:48.590 --> 00:20:51.690 align:middle line:84%
feeling more and more in
control each and every day.

00:20:51.690 --> 00:20:55.420 align:middle line:90%


00:20:55.420 --> 00:20:58.210 align:middle line:84%
You take a couple of
deep, refreshing breaths

00:20:58.210 --> 00:21:04.450 align:middle line:84%
in and out, perhaps
imagining breathing in calm,

00:21:04.450 --> 00:21:07.800 align:middle line:84%
pure, air, remembering
anxiety is simply

00:21:07.800 --> 00:21:14.480 align:middle line:84%
an old, primitive response,
which needs help to escape.

00:21:14.480 --> 00:21:17.330 align:middle line:84%
And as you exhale, you're
exhaling any feelings

00:21:17.330 --> 00:21:19.115 align:middle line:90%
of anxiety, stress, and panic.

00:21:19.115 --> 00:21:23.080 align:middle line:90%


00:21:23.080 --> 00:21:26.080 align:middle line:84%
And you can relax your body
if ever those old feelings

00:21:26.080 --> 00:21:30.160 align:middle line:84%
of panic return, breathing
deeply and calmly,

00:21:30.160 --> 00:21:35.060 align:middle line:84%
retraining your mind to slow
down instead of speed up,

00:21:35.060 --> 00:21:39.120 align:middle line:84%
rewiring those
thinking patterns,

00:21:39.120 --> 00:21:41.330 align:middle line:84%
allowing your body
and mind to relax

00:21:41.330 --> 00:21:43.100 align:middle line:90%
as you regain control now.

00:21:43.100 --> 00:21:49.280 align:middle line:90%


00:21:49.280 --> 00:21:51.410 align:middle line:84%
When you inhale in
this way, your breath

00:21:51.410 --> 00:21:58.820 align:middle line:84%
pushes deep into your
abdomen, deep, deep down.

00:21:58.820 --> 00:22:02.780 align:middle line:84%
You take slow, deep breaths
to regulate your breathing

00:22:02.780 --> 00:22:07.850 align:middle line:84%
and slowly let it go, whilst all
the same time telling yourself

00:22:07.850 --> 00:22:11.420 align:middle line:90%
to feel calm and relaxed.

00:22:11.420 --> 00:22:12.620 align:middle line:90%
I am calm.

00:22:12.620 --> 00:22:13.930 align:middle line:90%
I am confident.

00:22:13.930 --> 00:22:16.940 align:middle line:90%
I am strong.

00:22:16.940 --> 00:22:17.990 align:middle line:90%
I am calm.

00:22:17.990 --> 00:22:18.980 align:middle line:90%
I am confident.

00:22:18.980 --> 00:22:19.780 align:middle line:90%
I am strong.

00:22:19.780 --> 00:22:23.400 align:middle line:90%


00:22:23.400 --> 00:22:27.105 align:middle line:84%
You immediately feel much
calmer and much more relaxed.

00:22:27.105 --> 00:22:32.990 align:middle line:90%


00:22:32.990 --> 00:22:36.930 align:middle line:84%
You realize now that you
are not your thoughts.

00:22:36.930 --> 00:22:39.720 align:middle line:84%
Your thoughts are
merely old habits,

00:22:39.720 --> 00:22:42.600 align:middle line:84%
beliefs that have been formed
if they've been repeated

00:22:42.600 --> 00:22:44.360 align:middle line:90%
in your mind again and again.

00:22:44.360 --> 00:22:46.970 align:middle line:90%


00:22:46.970 --> 00:22:51.100 align:middle line:84%
So you decide to think
new, positive thoughts now,

00:22:51.100 --> 00:22:55.210 align:middle line:84%
empowering thoughts,
confident thoughts that

00:22:55.210 --> 00:22:58.630 align:middle line:84%
will equip you to stay calm and
relaxed throughout your day.

00:22:58.630 --> 00:23:01.670 align:middle line:90%


00:23:01.670 --> 00:23:05.360 align:middle line:84%
And as you think these
positive thoughts more often,

00:23:05.360 --> 00:23:09.260 align:middle line:84%
you slowly compound and
replace the old beliefs of I'm

00:23:09.260 --> 00:23:13.790 align:middle line:84%
feeling anxious to feeling
calm and relaxed, rewiring

00:23:13.790 --> 00:23:16.980 align:middle line:90%
those thinking patterns now.

00:23:16.980 --> 00:23:19.740 align:middle line:84%
As soon as you find yourself
thinking negatively,

00:23:19.740 --> 00:23:22.950 align:middle line:90%
you immediately replace--

00:23:22.950 --> 00:23:25.620 align:middle line:84%
I am feeling calm
and confident--

00:23:25.620 --> 00:23:28.730 align:middle line:90%


00:23:28.730 --> 00:23:31.390 align:middle line:84%
thinking more
positively day by day.

00:23:31.390 --> 00:23:35.550 align:middle line:90%


00:23:35.550 --> 00:23:38.670 align:middle line:84%
Your mind commands,
and your body obeys.

00:23:38.670 --> 00:23:42.300 align:middle line:84%
And when you tell yourself
that you're calm and relaxed,

00:23:42.300 --> 00:23:44.700 align:middle line:84%
you instantly
experience that calm,

00:23:44.700 --> 00:23:49.040 align:middle line:84%
relaxed feeling in your
body, taking back control.

00:23:49.040 --> 00:23:53.320 align:middle line:90%


00:23:53.320 --> 00:23:56.800 align:middle line:84%
And if you ever feel any of
that old anxiety creeping up

00:23:56.800 --> 00:24:02.640 align:middle line:84%
on you, all you need to do
is those breathing exercises

00:24:02.640 --> 00:24:05.880 align:middle line:84%
as quickly as possible,
reminding yourself

00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:08.280 align:middle line:90%
you can regulate your breathing.

00:24:08.280 --> 00:24:11.070 align:middle line:90%
You can relax your whole body.

00:24:11.070 --> 00:24:14.485 align:middle line:84%
You can, and you do,
immediately grounding yourself.

00:24:14.485 --> 00:24:18.920 align:middle line:90%


00:24:18.920 --> 00:24:22.370 align:middle line:84%
You remember to check
your body for tension.

00:24:22.370 --> 00:24:25.560 align:middle line:90%
And you release it.

00:24:25.560 --> 00:24:31.270 align:middle line:84%
Check your shoulders and neck,
letting your shoulders droop

00:24:31.270 --> 00:24:32.155 align:middle line:90%
and relax.

00:24:32.155 --> 00:24:36.670 align:middle line:90%


00:24:36.670 --> 00:24:38.590 align:middle line:84%
You check your
jaw, and you allow

00:24:38.590 --> 00:24:43.580 align:middle line:84%
it to hang loosely,
your forehead becoming

00:24:43.580 --> 00:24:44.790 align:middle line:90%
smooth and relaxed.

00:24:44.790 --> 00:24:47.340 align:middle line:90%


00:24:47.340 --> 00:24:52.800 align:middle line:84%
You check your abdomen, letting
each breath relax your stomach.

00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:56.340 align:middle line:84%
And each deep breath
relaxes your stomach

00:24:56.340 --> 00:24:59.630 align:middle line:90%
more and more deeply.

00:24:59.630 --> 00:25:05.310 align:middle line:84%
You relax any part of your
body that feels the tension,

00:25:05.310 --> 00:25:06.310 align:middle line:90%
letting it go.

00:25:06.310 --> 00:25:10.640 align:middle line:90%


00:25:10.640 --> 00:25:14.730 align:middle line:84%
You always remember
that you are in charge.

00:25:14.730 --> 00:25:18.260 align:middle line:84%
You have the ability, the
tools, and the knowledge

00:25:18.260 --> 00:25:21.515 align:middle line:84%
to let go of all of that
old, unnecessary anxiety.

00:25:21.515 --> 00:25:25.060 align:middle line:90%


00:25:25.060 --> 00:25:27.550 align:middle line:84%
You feel confident,
calm, and relaxed.

00:25:27.550 --> 00:25:32.440 align:middle line:90%


00:25:32.440 --> 00:25:37.000 align:middle line:84%
From now on, you find yourself
feeling much calmer and much

